Final arguments are set to begin in the Air India bombing trial involving Sikh extremists in Canada who built and checked suitcase bombs onto Vancouver flights.
Two Sikh journalists were assassinated, and the prosecution relies on women close to the accused.
Ajaib Singh Bagri and Ripudaman Singh Malik face charges in the deadliest terrorist act before 9/11.
The prosecution alleges revenge for India's actions against Sikhs in the 1980s.
The trial, heard by Justice Ian Bruce Josephson without a jury, is nearing a verdict after 19 months.
Despite challenges, justice for the 329 victims is finally within reach.
